      "content": "That makes sense. Let's try to put that into practice. Can you actually write out a short scene using that approach? \n\nMaybe a scene at a local diner or a private office where three men—let's call them Mr. Henderson, Mr. Miller, and Mr. Vance—are discussing the recent influx of people who don't \"fit the tradition\" of the town. I want to see that condescending tone you mentioned. They shouldn't be yelling; they should be acting like they're just being \"practical\" about protecting their families and their property. Show how they rationalize their desire for segregation or restricted movement as just \"preserving the peace\" or \"keeping things the way they should be.\" I'm looking for that specific way they would justify these systemic exclusions through \"polite\" conversation.",
